    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Formats of paintings, prints, photographs, sculptures, or other works or other things that fall within a large range of size for the norm. For example, the term is used for film format in photography, usually reserved for sheet film formats 4x5 inches and larger, but may be extended to describe the fields of related imaging detectors, or spectroscopic equipment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
